            End if

        Else if choice is 3
            If data not loaded
                Print "Load data first"
            Else
                Ask for course number
                Search and print course info
            End if

        Else if choice is 9
            Print "Goodbye"
            End program

        Else
            Print "Invalid option"

    End While

End Function


Vector Pseudocode

The vector is the simplest approach. Everything is stored in a list.

Load Courses:
Function loadCoursesVector(fileName, courseList)

    Open file

    If file fails to open
        Print error and stop

    Create list of courseNumbers

    First pass through file
        Store all course numbers

    Second pass through file
        Create Course objects

        For each prerequisite
            If not in courseNumbers
                Print error and stop

        Add course to courseList

    Close file

End Function


Print All Courses:
Function printAllCoursesVector(courseList)

    Sort courseList by courseNumber

    For each course
        Print courseNumber and courseTitle

End Function


Search and Print One Course:
Function printCourseVector(courseList, courseNumber)

    Loop through courseList

        If match found
            Print course info and prerequisites
            Return

    Print "Course not found"

End Function



Hash Table Pseudocode

The hash table stores courses based on a key (course number).

Hash Function:
Function hash(courseNumber)
    total = sum of ASCII values
    Return total mod tableSize
End Function


Load Courses:
Function loadCoursesHash(fileName, hashTable)

    Open file

    Create list of allCourseNumbers
    Create list of courses

    Read file and store all courses

    Validate all prerequisites exist

    Insert each course into hashTable

End Function


Insert:
Function insertCourseHash(hashTable, course)

